 467, \"to\": 486}, {\"ngram\": \"(Springer\", \"from\": 488, \"to\": 497}]}, {\"sentence\": \"2023).\", \"from\": 499, \"to\": 505, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The article reflects the author's opinions and not necessarily the views of CGTN.\", \"from\": 506, \"to\": 587, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The article\", \"from\": 506, \"to\": 517}, {\"ngram\": \"the author's opinions\", \"from\": 527, \"to\": 548}, {\"ngram\": \"not necessarily the views\", \"from\": 553, \"to\": 578}, {\"ngram\": \"CGTN\", \"from\": 582, \"to\": 586}]}, {\"sentence\": \"International relations are deteriorating, mutual mistrust between states is growing, the cold-war atmosphere is intensifying, and bloody conflicts are taking place, especially in Ukraine and the Gaza Strip.\", \"from\": 589, \"to\": 796, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 769, \"end\": 776, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ukraine\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.164589244384865e-14, \"text\": \"Ukraine\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ukraine\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ukraine\"}, {\"begin\": 785, \"end\": 795, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gaza_Strip\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.074464931470481e-15, \"text\": \"Gaza Strip\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gaza_Strip\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gaza_Strip\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"International relations\", \"from\": 589, \"to\": 612}, {\"ngram\": \"mutual mistrust\", \"from\": 632, \"to\": 647}, {\"ngram\": \"states\", \"from\": 656, \"to\": 662}, {\"ngram\": \"the cold-war atmosphere\", \"from\": 675, \"to\": 698}, {\"ngram\": \"bloody conflicts\", \"from\": 720, \"to\": 736}, {\"ngram\": \"place\", \"from\": 748, \"to\": 753}]}, {\"sentence\": \"By no means it has to be that way, and yet it is and will be for some time to come.\", \"from\": 797, \"to\": 880, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"no means\", \"from\": 800, \"to\": 808}, {\"ngram\": \"that way\", \"from\": 822, \"to\": 830}, {\"ngram\": \"some time\", \"from\": 862, \"to\": 871}]}, {\"sentence\": \"No one knows for how long.\", \"from\": 881, \"to\": 907, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"No one\", \"from\": 881, \"to\": 887}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The drama of the situation lies in the fact that in various countries the forces pushing for clashes rather than peaceful dialogue tend to be more influential.\", \"from\": 909, \"to\": 1068, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The drama\", \"from\": 909, \"to\": 918}, {\"ngram\": \"the situation\", \"from\": 922, \"to\": 935}, {\"ngram\": \"the fact\", \"from\": 944, \"to\": 952}, {\"ngram\": \"various countries\", \"from\": 961, \"to\": 978}, {\"ngram\": \"the forces\", \"from\": 979, \"to\": 989}, {\"ngram\": \"clashes\", \"from\": 1002, \"to\": 1009}, {\"ngram\": \"peaceful dialogue\", \"from\": 1022, \"to\": 1039}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Pro-war pressure groups in certain Western countries are more powerful than peaceful political circles.\", \"from\": 1069, \"to\": 1173, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1105, \"end\": 1112, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Western_world\", \"score\": 0.9999999999936335, \"rank\": 6.597828187704961e-12, \"text\": \"Western\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Western_world\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Western_world\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Pro-war pressure groups\", \"from\": 1069, \"to\": 1092}, {\"ngram\": \"peaceful political circles\", \"from\": 1145, \"to\": 1171}]}, {\"sentence\": \"One of the stupidest sentences in history is being thoughtlessly promoted: If you want peace, get ready for war.\", \"from\": 1174, \"to\": 1286, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the stupidest sentences\", \"from\": 1181, \"to\": 1204}, {\"ngram\": \"history\", \"from\": 1208, \"to\": 1215}, {\"ngram\": \"peace\", \"from\": 1261, \"to\": 1266}, {\"ngram\": \"war\", \"from\": 1282, \"to\": 1285}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Well, no; if one desires peace, one must get ready for it rather than spend a fortune to arm oneself to the teeth, which can be knocked out by others arming themselves.\", \"from\": 1288, \"to\": 1456, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"peace\", \"from\": 1313, \"to\": 1318}, {\"ngram\": \"one\", \"from\": 1320, \"to\": 1323}, {\"ngram\": \"a fortune\", \"from\": 1364, \"to\": 1373}, {\"ngram\": \"oneself\", \"from\": 1381, \"to\": 1388}, {\"ngram\": \"the teeth\", \"from\": 1392, \"to\": 1401}, {\"ngram\": \"others\", \"from\": 1431, \"to\": 1437}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Today, even a minor incident can lead to a major disaster.\", \"from\": 1457, \"to\": 1515, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"even a minor incident\", \"from\": 1464, \"to\": 1485}, {\"ngram\": \"a major disaster\", \"from\": 1498, \"to\": 1514}]}, {\"sentence\": \"But still, it is not too late.\", \"from\": 1516, \"to\": 1546, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"For every action, there is a reaction.\", \"from\": 1548, \"to\": 1586, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"every action\", \"from\": 1552, \"to\": 1564}, {\"ngram\": \"a reaction\", \"from\": 1575, \"to\": 1585}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The spiral of military spending is getting momentum.\", \"from\": 1587, \"to\": 1639, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The spiral\", \"from\": 1587, \"to\": 1597}, {\"ngram\": \"military spending\", \"from\": 1601, \"to\": 1618}, {\"ngram\": \"momentum\", \"from\": 1630, \"to\": 1638}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In 2023, the world spent a record $2.4 trillion on armaments, 6.8 percent more than in the previous year, according to the Stockholm International Peace Research Institute (SIPRI).\", \"from\": 1640, \"to\": 1820, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1763, \"end\": 1819, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Stockholm_International_Peace_Research_Institute\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Stockholm International Peace Research Institute (SIPRI)\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Stockholm_International_Peace_Research_Institute\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Stockholm_International_Peace_Research_Institute\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the world\", \"from\": 1649, \"to\": 1658}, {\"ngram\": \"a record\", \"from\": 1665, \"to\": 1673}, {\"ngram\": \"armaments\", \"from\": 1691, \"to\": 1700}, {\"ngram\": \"the previous year\", \"from\": 1727, \"to\": 1744}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The world military burden, which is defined as military spending as a percentage of global GDP, increased to 2.3 percent in 2023.\", \"from\": 1821, \"to\": 1950, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The world military burden\", \"from\": 1821, \"to\": 1846}, {\"ngram\": \"military spending\", \"from\": 1868, \"to\": 1885}, {\"ngram\": \"a percentage\", \"from\": 1889, \"to\": 1901}, {\"ngram\": \"global GDP\", \"from\": 1905, \"to\": 1915}, {\"ngram\": \"2.3 percent\", \"from\": 1930, \"to\": 1941}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Meanwhile, there is not enough money for healthcare and education, infrastructure development, and combating disastrous global warming, not to mention culture and science.\", \"from\": 1951, \"to\": 2122, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"enough money\", \"from\": 1975, \"to\": 1987}, {\"ngram\": \"healthcare\", \"from\": 1992, \"to\": 2002}, {\"ngram\": \"education\", \"from\": 2007, \"to\": 2016}, {\"ngram\": \"infrastructure development\", \"from\": 2018, \"to\": 2044}, {\"ngram\": \"disastrous global warming\", \"from\": 2060, \"to\": 2085}, {\"ngram\": \"culture\", \"from\": 2102, \"to\": 2109}, {\"ngram\": \"science\", \"from\": 2114, \"to\": 2121}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It is obvious that because of various conflicts of ideas and interests, maintaining security requires keeping a balance of power.\", \"from\": 2124, \"to\": 2253, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"various conflicts\", \"from\": 2154, \"to\": 2171}, {\"ngram\": \"ideas\", \"from\": 2175, \"to\": 2180}, {\"ngram\": \"interests\", \"from\": 2185, \"to\": 2194}, {\"ngram\": \"security\", \"from\": 2208, \"to\": 2216}, {\"ngram\": \"a balance\", \"from\": 2234, \"to\": 2243}, {\"ngram\": \"power\", \"from\": 2247, \"to\": 2252}]}, {\"sentence\": \"But the trick is to achieve such a desired state at the lowest possible cost, not with ever greater outlays.\", \"from\": 2254, \"to\": 2362, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the trick\", \"from\": 2258, \"to\": 2267}, {\"ngram\": \"such a desired state\", \"from\": 2282, \"to\": 2302}, {\"ngram\": \"the lowest possible cost\", \"from\": 2306, \"to\": 2330}, {\"ngram\": \"ever greater outlays\", \"from\": 2341, \"to\": 2361}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Unfortunately, the latter is the case in several countries, starting from the NATO members grandly celebrating the bloc's 75th anniversary.\", \"from\": 2363, \"to\": 2502, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2441, \"end\": 2445, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NATO\", \"score\": 0.9999999999972715, \"rank\": 2.5844682860562786e-12, \"text\": \"NATO\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NATO\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NATO\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the case\", \"from\": 2392, \"to\": 2400}, {\"ngram\": \"several countries\", \"from\": 2404, \"to\": 2421}, {\"ngram\": \"the bloc's 75th anniversary\", \"from\": 2474, \"to\": 2501}]}, {\"sentence\": \"NATO Secretary-General Jens Stoltenberg announced that in 2024, 23 out of the 32 total member countries will meet or exceed the target of spending at least 2 percent of GDP on defense.\", \"from\": 2503, \"to\": 2687, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2503, \"end\": 2507, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NATO\", \"score\": 0.9999999999972715, \"rank\": 2.5844682860562786e-12, \"text\": \"NATO\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NATO\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NATO\"}, {\"begin\": 2526, \"end\": 2542, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jens_Stoltenberg\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Jens Stoltenberg\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jens_Stoltenberg\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jens_Stoltenberg\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the 32 total member countries\", \"from\": 2577, \"to\": 2606}, {\"ngram\": \"the target\", \"from\": 2627, \"to\": 2637}, {\"ngram\": \"spending\", \"from\": 2641, \"to\": 2649}, {\"ngram\": \"at least 2 percent\", \"from\": 2650, \"to\": 2668}, {\"ngram\": \"GDP\", \"from\": 2672, \"to\": 2675}, {\"ngram\": \"defense\", \"from\": 2679, \"to\": 2686}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The biggest arms spender is the U.S. with $916 billion.\", \"from\": 2689, \"to\": 2744, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The biggest arms spender\", \"from\": 2689, \"to\": 2713}, {\"ngram\": \"the U.S.\", \"from\": 2717, \"to\": 2725}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It is no wonder that their budget deficit is approaching 7 percent of GDP, and massive public debt is growing, approaching 100 percent of GDP, threatening to destabilize its economy.\", \"from\": 2745, \"to\": 2927, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"no wonder\", \"from\": 2751, \"to\": 2760}, {\"ngram\": \"their budget deficit\", \"from\": 2766, \"to\": 2786}, {\"ngram\": \"7 percent\", \"from\": 2802, \"to\": 2811}, {\"ngram\": \"GDP\", \"from\": 2815, \"to\": 2818}, {\"ngram\": \"massive public debt\", \"from\": 2824, \"to\": 2843}, {\"ngram\": \"100 percent\", \"from\": 2868, \"to\": 2879}, {\"ngram\": \"GDP\", \"from\": 2883, \"to\": 2886}, {\"ngram\": \"its economy\", \"from\": 2915, \"to\": 2926}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The American industrial-military lobby, together with the parties they finance and the corrupt media, is so strong that peaceful voices are effectively silenced.\", \"from\": 2928, \"to\": 3089, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2932, \"end\": 2940, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.1336663136475834e-13, \"text\": \"American\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the parties\", \"from\": 2982, \"to\": 2993}, {\"ngram\": \"the corrupt media\", \"from\": 3011, \"to\": 3028}, {\"ngram\": \"peaceful voices\", \"from\": 3048, \"to\": 3063}]}, {\"sentence\": \"More than half of the global military spending - $1.3 trillion - is made by NATO.\", \"from\": 3091, \"to\": 3172, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3167, \"end\": 3171, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NATO\", \"score\": 0.9999999999972715, \"rank\": 2.5844682860562786e-12, \"text\": \"NATO\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NATO\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NATO\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"More than half\", \"from\": 3091, \"to\": 3105}, {\"ngram\": \"the global military spending\", \"from\": 3109, \"to\": 3137}]}, {\"sentence\": \"European member states share 28 percent of these costs, in total spending over three times more than Russia, which allocated the equivalent of only $109 billion, equivalent to 5.9 percent of its GDP.\", \"from\": 3173, \"to\": 3372, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3274, \"end\": 3280, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Russia\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.8944806087779017e-15, \"text\": \"Russia\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Russia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Russia\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"European member states\", \"from\": 3173, \"to\": 3195}, {\"ngram\": \"28 percent\", \"from\": 3202, \"to\": 3212}, {\"ngram\": \"these costs\", \"from\": 3216, \"to\": 3227}, {\"ngram\": \"total spending\", \"from\": 3232, \"to\": 3246}, {\"ngram\": \"the equivalent\", \"from\": 3298, \"to\": 3312}, {\"ngram\": \"5.9 percent\", \"from\": 3349, \"to\": 3360}, {\"ngram\": \"its GDP\", \"from\": 3364, \"to\": 3371}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Though taking the purchasing power parity into account it is the equivalent of almost $400 billion, according to estimates by SIPRI, it is still a third less than the expenditures of the European NATO countries.\", \"from\": 3373, \"to\": 3584, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3499, \"end\": 3504, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Stockholm_International_Peace_Research_Institute\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"SIPRI\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Stockholm_International_Peace_Research_Institute\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Stockholm_International_Peace_Research_Institute\"}, {\"begin\": 3569, \"end\": 3573, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NATO\", \"score\": 0.9999999999972715, \"rank\": 2.5844682860562786e-12, \"text\": \"NATO\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NATO\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NATO\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the purchasing power parity\", \"from\": 3387, \"to\": 3414}, {\"ngram\": \"account\", \"from\": 3420, \"to\": 3427}, {\"ngram\": \"the equivalent\", \"from\": 3434, \"to\": 3448}, {\"ngram\": \"estimates\", \"from\": 3486, \"to\": 3495}, {\"ngram\": \"the expenditures\", \"from\": 3536, \"to\": 3552}]}, {\"sentence\": \"If only the members of the European Union are considered, their aggregated military budgets still exceed that of Russia.\", \"from\": 3585, \"to\": 3705, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3621, \"end\": 3626, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 6.1413726390035615e-27, \"text\": \"Union\",